com.dukes.klein.scanner

Class Inputter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.dukes.klein.scanner.Inputter
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    FileInputter, StringInputter

    public abstract class Inputter
extends Object
    Describes an object that iterates over an entire object for characters. Now, we chose to not use the Iterator interface, as it would not allow for primitive chars to be read. This is why this class is included.
    Since:
    1.0

    • Method Detail

      • currentChar

        public char currentChar()
        Returns the character at the current position of the parser.
        Returns:
        The current character.

      • next

        public void next()
        Returns the next character within the inputter. This is the only method that should increment the position variable. Making position protected allows classes that need to maniuplate position available to it, but this method will automatically increment the position by one.

      • hasNext

        public abstract boolean hasNext()
        Determines whether there is another character in the inputter object.
        Returns:
        true if there is another character in the parser, false otherwise.

      • lookAhead

        public abstract char lookAhead()
        Looks ahead in the inputter without consuming the current character. This method has undefined behaviour at the end of the parser.
        Returns:
        The next character in the stream, if there is one.
